    "(6) Fully connected neural networksThe simplest procedure is to approximate the operator F with a FC-NN F F N N.û(x) = F F N N (λ; x; θ) (7)Example applications are flow classification [68,69], fluid flow in turbomachinery [70], dynamic beam displacements from previous measurements [71], wall velocity predictions in turbulence [72], heat transfer [73], prediction of source terms in turbulence models [74], full waveform inversion [75][76][77], and topology optimization based on moving morphable bars [78].",
